1. HTML (The Structure)

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the foundation of a webpage. It creates the structure, like the "skeleton" of a web page.
Basic HTML Page

html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My First Web Page</title>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Welcome to My Page</h1>
  <p>This is my first webpage! I'm learning HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>

</body>
</html>

Explanation

    <!DOCTYPE html>: Tells the browser this is an HTML5 document.
    <html>: The root of your HTML document.
    <head>: Contains meta-information about the page (like the title).
    <body>: The main content area. Here we add headings and paragraphs.
    <h1> and <p>: These tags are for headings and paragraphs. They display text on the page.

2. CSS (Styling the Page)

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) controls the style and appearance of HTML elements. Letâ€™s add some color and style!
Adding CSS

Add the CSS inside the <style> tag in the <head> section.

html

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My First Web Page</title>
  <style>
