Explanation

    background-color: Sets the page's background color.
    font-family: Sets the font style.
    color: Changes the text color.
    text-align: Centers the text in the middle of the page.

3. JavaScript (Making It Interactive)

JavaScript is a programming language that makes a page interactive. Letâ€™s add a button that displays a message when clicked.
Adding JavaScript

Add this inside the <body> section:

html

<body>

  <h1>Welcome to My Page</h1>
  <p>This is my first webpage! I'm learning HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>

  <button onclick="showMessage()">Click Me!</button>

  <script>
    function showMessage() {
      alert("Hello! You clicked the button!");
    }
  </script>

</body>

Explanation

    <button>: Creates a clickable button.
    onclick: Calls a JavaScript function when the button is clicked.
    JavaScript Function: Inside the <script> tags, showMessage() is a function that shows an alert box with a message when called.

